Package com.example.javafx_clinicmanager

package com.example.javafx_clinicmanager
  • Class
    Description
    Appointment
    The Appointment class models an appointment in a scheduling system.
    ClinicManagerController
    The Controller class is a management class for the Clinic Manager JavaFX application.
    ClinicManagerMain
    The ClinicManagerMain class is an entry point for the Clinic Manager JavaFX application.
    Date
    The Date Class models the Date system for the logic of the software
    Doctor
    This is the Doctor class that hold Doctor info, it is an extension of Provider class, it holds the speciality and npi number of the Docotor
    Imaging
    This class is an Extension of Appointment class, it is for Imagining Room appointments
    List<E>
    The List List class that implements a simple array-based list for Appointment and Provider.
    Location
    The Location enum represents various city location with county and zip code, of medical service providers practice.
    Patient
    The Patient class defines a Patient with a profile and visits.
    Person
    This is a Super class Person for subclasses Patient and Provider
    Profile
    The Profile class defines a Profile with a first name, last name, and date of birth.
    Provider
    This is a superclass for Doctor and Technician, and is also subclass of Person
    Radiology
    This is enum class for Imaging rooms
    RotationList
    This class represents the circular linked list to manage rotation of technician.
    Sort
    This class does all the sorting for list of appointment, providers, and patients.
    Specialty
    The Specialty enum represents different field in medical and contain charge for each.
    Technician
    This the subclass of Provider
    Timeslot
    This class handles the Time of the appointments
    Visit
    The Visit class keeps track of visit using linked list to store those visits.
